   - Show notification balloon after profile apply

7. Persistence:
   - Use PersistentStateComponent / modern service-based persistence
   - Store profiles in the IDE config safely
   - Keep the stored data format versioned for future migrations

8. Architecture:
   - Use Java (latest compatible SDK)
   - Use Gradle with the IntelliJ Platform Gradle Plugin
   - Target current stable IntelliJ Platform APIs suitable for Community Edition
   - Organize the code cleanly:
     - model
     - services
     - actions
     - settings UI
     - display detection / rules
     - settings appliers
   - Prefer testable service abstractions over giant action classes

9. Compatibility:
   - Must support IntelliJ IDEA Community
   - Design for modern JetBrains Platform builds
   - Avoid deprecated APIs where practical
